---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Card from "@components/Card.astro";
import Button from "@components/Button.astro";
const title = 'Work With Me';
const description = 'Bounded escalation formats for SAP BTP extension failures that have crossed from implementation into architectural decision failure.';
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <!-- 1) Context intro -->
  <section class="stack tight">
    <h1>Independent architectural verdicts.</h1>
    <p class="measure">These are bounded escalation formats for situations that have crossed from implementation into architectural decision failure. The output is a written verdict that defines what must change, what must remain, and where jurisdiction sits.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- 2) Decision‑level verdict (placed first) -->
  <section class="stack">
    <Card eyebrow="Verdict" title="Executive Boundary Verdict" class="emphasis">
      <h3>When this is the right move</h3>
      <p class="measure">Competing architectural truths cannot reconcile; no team can legitimately approve the next change. Decision impasse around trust, routing, identity, tenant, or lifecycle authority.</p>
      <h3>What you send</h3>
      <p class="measure">Landscape, runtime divergence, timeline of change, ownership map, and the decision that cannot converge.</p>
      <h3>What you receive</h3>
      <p class="measure">A formal written verdict that defines what must change, what must remain, and who holds jurisdiction. Legible follow‑ons you can escalate internally.</p>
      <h3>What this is not</h3>
      <p class="measure">Not a rescue project, not implementation takeover, not a blame exercise.</p>
      <Button href="/contact/" variant="primary">Assess applicability</Button>
    </Card>
  </section>

  <!-- 3) Engagement spectrum (light → heavy) -->
  <h2>Engagement spectrum</h2>
  <section class="feature">
    <Card eyebrow="Rapid" title="Rapid Boundary Triage">
      <h3>When</h3>
      <p class="measure">High‑signal incident with one or two competing narratives; Postman vs App Router/Work Zone mismatch; single‑tenant variance.</p>
      <h3>What you send</h3>
      <p class="measure">Minimal landscape and the failing path(s); specific divergence examples.</p>
      <h3>What you receive</h3>
      <p class="measure">Boundary map across the six boundaries, top decision points, and a written memo with a provisional verdict.</p>
      <h3>Not</h3>
      <p class="measure">Not a substitute for operational support or ticket execution.</p>
      <Button href="/contact/" variant="ghost">Request triage review</Button>
    </Card>
    <Card eyebrow="Audit" title="Boundary Audit">
      <h3>When</h3>
      <p class="measure">Fragmented ownership across teams/vendors; recurring incidents; rollout instability months after go‑live.</p>
      <h3>What you send</h3>
      <p class="measure">Landscape, divergence, stakeholder map, and representative incidents.</p>
      <h3>What you receive</h3>
      <p class="measure">Jurisdiction‑based ownership mapping, structural remediation rules, and decision points prepared for executive verdict if required.</p>
      <h3>Not</h3>
      <p class="measure">Not staff augmentation, not indefinite advisory.</p>
      <Button href="/contact/" variant="ghost">Request scope discussion</Button>
    </Card>
  </section>

  <!-- 4) Why the spectrum exists (transition) -->
  <section class="stack compact">
    <p class="measure">All formats produce architectural judgment. Only the Executive Boundary Verdict defines final jurisdiction.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- 5) What I do not sell -->
  <h2>Why this is different from another round of implementation review</h2>
  <p class="measure">Implementation reviews test local correctness. Verdicts establish final jurisdiction across boundaries. When runtime behavior diverges by tenant or entry path, the problem is not more fixes — it is the absence of a legitimate architectural decision.</p>

  <h2>What I do not sell</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No implementation or delivery services.</li>
    <li>No staff augmentation or ticket execution.</li>
    <li>No generic advisory funnels.</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- 6) Initiation protocol -->
  <h2>Initiation protocol</h2>
  <p class="measure">Send a concise structured summary. The next step is a fixed‑scope triage, audit, or verdict — not a sales funnel.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Landscape (S/4 + BTP runtimes + identity)</li>
    <li>Observable runtime divergence (by tenant or surface)</li>
    <li>Timeline of change</li>
    <li>Stakeholder ownership</li>
    <li>The decision that cannot converge</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:pei_jiandong@hotmail.com">pei_jiandong@hotmail.com</a> or <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/peijiandong/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
